{"word":"θῆσσα","slug":"θῆσσα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θῆσσα1</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a poor girl, one obliged to go out for hire</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <el>θῆσσα τράπεζα</el> <i>menial</i> fare, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>From <el>ΘΕ</el>, Root of <a href='S:τίθημι'><el>τίθημι</el></a>, <i>a settler.</i>\n <hr/> <el><b>θῆσσα</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <el>θής</el>, <a href='S:quod vide'>q. <a href='S:vide'>v.</a></a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>Greek form of <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>thensa, a sacred car</el>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}